  <slide>
    <title>Keyboard Support: Testing</title>
    <contents>
      <ul>
        <li>Move your mouse away from your work station or cover your track pad to allow your attention to be only on using the keyboard.  <br/><em>Note: Recommend using Firefox since it's default focus styling is less apparent than Chrome or Safari.</em></li>
        <li>Use the <kbd>tab</kbd> key to navigate to links, form controls and other interactive content on the page.</li>
        <li>Questions:
          <ul>
            <li>Can I tell where keyboard focus is on the page?</li>
            <li>Using the <kbd>Tab</kbd> can I navigate to all the links and form controls on the page.</li>
            <li>Can I <em>activate</em> links, buttons, checkboxes and radio buttons using the <kbd>Space</kbd> or <kbd>Enter</kbd> keys?</li>
            <li>Does the navigation of links and form controls seem predictable?</li>
            <li>Does focus ever <em>disappear</em> and then magically reapear?</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </contents>
  </slide>

